Tavatron turned to Dinobot:

"It appears you made a wise decision. I would have done the same, had I been 
in a similiar situation." Tavatron stops walking, and spends a moment gazing 
at the immense doors of the ark. She turns and looks at Dinobot:

"I wanted to thank you for the training. I know I still have much to learn, 
and at times may lose track of myself." Tavatron looks to the side, "Perhaps 
we could practice again." Tavatron looks at Dinobot's optics, searching for 
an answer.
